sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1320000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Cd sensitive promoter with Ogr activator, PO promoter, and GFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This composite is composed of parts already in the registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The cadmium sensitive promoter catalyzes the production of the Ogr activator. The activator triggers the PO promoter causing the production of GFP at greater levels than the cadmium promoter alone.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Will Reiber

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: GFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: green fluorescent protein derived from jellyfish Aequeora victoria wild-type GFP (SwissProt: P42212
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: GFP (mut3b) [note that this part does not have a barcode]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: jcbraff

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I746350
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: plasmid DNA supplied by Prof. Richard Calendar, University of California.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The ogr activator taken from P2 phage acts on a class of inducible promoters (parts I746360 to I746365), inducing their activity to varying degrees. The part sequence does already contain a ribosome binding site (B0034)!
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The part does contain a RBS (B0034) already.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stefan Milde

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K174016
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part purely holds the binding site for ArsR protein which can be released when bound to different metals. Hence this part can be combined with any promoter to sense metals that can bind to ArsR protein. When added in front of a promoter with another metal sensor's protein's binding site, it can form an AND gate to sensitively detect specific metals.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It was developed mainly to use combinatorial approaches for metal sensing.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: The Newcastle 2009 iGEM team

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K174017
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: CadA promoter with CzrA binding site
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It is taken from ''B. subtilis'' ''cadA'' promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
In ''B. subtilis'' CadA system works as an efflux system to take the metals out in the cell. It is normally repressed by CzrA repressor protein. When certain metals get inside the cell, they can bind to CzrA and derepress the promoter expressing CadA. Hence metals are taken out by the efflux system.
By taking the promoter of CadA system, we created a generic metal sensor. Hence when it is combined with coding sequences of other genes, it will regulate the expression of these genes upon sensing metals.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It was developed mainly to use combinatorial approaches for metal sensing
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: The Newcastle 2009 iGEM team

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I746361
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The source of the DNA is the P2 phage genome.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the PO promoter taken from the P2 phage genome. It is an inducible promoter that is activated by a class of activators, including P2 ogr (I746350), PSP3 pag (I746351) and phiR73 delta (I746352). These different activators should cause different levels of activity of the PO promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stefan Milde
